Introduction

Software development is fundamentally a continuous process [17,
21, 28]. Real-world projects evolve over weeks, months, and years
through iterative cycles of planning, implementation, testing, and
revision [8, 27, 34]. Engineers join and leave teams, priorities shift
as requirements change, and the scope of work adapts in response
to emerging constraints and discoveries [19, 36, 53]. Recent Large
