Figure 1: Hedwig is a CLI coding agent that dynamically calibrates its level of autonomy in response to user interactions and
feedback. Hedwig records and reasons over user interactions (e.g., code edits, plan corrections, rejected/approved commands)
over time to maintain an evolving set of behavioral policies. These policies are used to govern the agent’s actions and frequency
